	<main>
		<img width="2500" height="1200" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-haida-title.jpg" class="singlepostthumb wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-haida-title.jpg 2500w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-haida-title-520x250.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-haida-title-1200x576.jpg 1200w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-haida-title-768x369.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-haida-title-1536x737.jpg 1536w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-haida-title-2048x983.jpg 2048w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-haida-title-900x432.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /><div class="post-thumbnail-caption">Gaagwiis (Jason Alsop), president of the Council of the Haida Nation, signs the historic Gaayhllxid/Gíihlagalgang “Rising Tide” Haida Title Lands Agreement in April 2024, with British Columbia premier David Eby, center, and Haida vice president Stephen Grosse, second from left, looking on. Photo by Felipe Fittipaldi/Province of British Columbia</div>
			<article class="main container col4">
								<header class="maincol">
										<h1 class="pagetitle">In Coastal British Columbia, the Haida Get Their Land Back</h1>
										<h2 class="dek singlepagecontainer">By affirming Indigenous land ownership, British Columbia and the Haida Nation are signaling a new era for Indigenous relations.</h2>
										<section class="singlebyline singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Authored by</h3>
						by  
										<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/serena-renner/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_top" >Serena Renner</a>								<br/>
												</section>
					 
					<aside class="singlebydatewords singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Wordcount</h3>
						April 22, 2024 | 1,700 words, about 8 minutes
					</aside>

					
				</header>

				
